get.description: Get dataset by id. Example: Artportalen - Fladdermöss

404.description: Not Found - The requested dataset doesn't exist

parameters.name: take
parameters.description: Format - int32. Number of items to return. 1000 items is the max to return in one call.

404.description: Not Found - The requested event doesn't exist

parameters.name: take
parameters.description: Format - int32. Number of items to return. 1000 items is the max to return in one call.

get.description: Get occurrence by Id. Example: urn:lsid:artportalen.se:sighting:98571689

parameters.name: take
parameters.description: Format - int32. Number of items to return. 1000 items is the max to return in one call.

AccessRights.description: Information about whether the whole, parts of, or nothing in the dataset is publically available.

Activity.description: Activity or behavior of the observed organism.

license.description: States which Creative Commons license that is applied to the attachment.

rightsHolder.description: States who the creator of the attachment is.

AssociatedMediaType.description: Format of attachment, e.g. image, video, sound, pdf etc.

BasisOfRecord.description: The type of species observation the record deals with (e.g. human observation, material sample etc.)

Cloudiness.description: States the cloud condtions during the survey event.

CoordinateSystem.description: Coordinate system for the (X, Y) coordinates of the geometry.

identifier.description: The dataset id-number within the metadata catalogue administered by the authority that is responsible for the information.

license.description: States which Creative Commons license that is applied to the dataset.  Note that any attachments included in the dataset have their own separate licenses.

title.description: Name of the dataset. Can sometimes be the same as the name of the project.

creator.description: The organisation responsible for the data collection. More than  one organisation can be given here.

dataStewardship.description: Name of the data stewardship within which the dataset is handled.

description.description: Short description of the dataset or the context for collection of the data included in the dataset. The structure and content of the description is governed by the requirements from the respective metadata catalogues.

methodology.description: The methodology that is used for the data collection, e.g. as described by one or more monitoring manuals. Can contain a range of methods for the same and/or different parts of the data collection.

spatial.description: The country in which the data in the dataset were collected in.

descriptionAccessRights.description: When the dataset is not public or access is restricted  (see the property accessRights), how and/or why is described here.

metadatalanguage.description: The language that is used when writing metadata about the dataset.

language.description: The language used in the dataset.

eventIds.description: A list of unique identites for surveys that is part of the dataset.

skip.description: Ignores the specified number of items and returns a sequence starting at the item after the last skipped item.

totalCount.description: The total number of records matching the query.

startDate.description: Event start date specified in the ISO 8601 standard. If no timezone is specified, GMT+1 (CEST) is assumed

endDate.description: Event end date specified in the ISO 8601 standard. If no timezone is specified, GMT+1 (CEST) is assumed

eventID.description: A unique id for the survey event within a specific dataset hosted by the respective datahosts. A survey event is usually a visit to a survey area/site. A survey event can also be a visit to a smaller defined part of a survey area/site or one of several samples from the same place. The term survey event can also represent a specific period or season. What eventID is representing is given in the attribute eventType.

eventType.description: States what the survey event (eventID) is representing, e.g. a visit, part visit, sample, period, season etc.

parentEventID.description: A unique id that groups several related visits, e.g. all visits to the different subparts within a survey location, or all visits to all survey locations that were made during a season. Example: EventID for a survey event at a location becomes the parentID for all the visits to the different subparts. EventID for a season becomes the parentID for all the visits to all locations within the survey programme.

eventStartDate.description: Date and Time for when the survey started (local time).

eventEndDate.description: Date and Time for when the survey ended (local time).

plainStartDate.description: Start date of the event in the format yyyy-MM-dd.

plainEndDate.description: End date of the event in the format yyyy-MM-dd.

plainStartTime.description: Start time of the event in W. Europe Standard Time formatted as hh:mm.

plainEndTime.description: End time of the event in W. Europe Standard Time formatted as hh:mm.

locationProtected.description: States whether the position of a location is protected. The true position for a protected location is shown only to authorized persons. To others the position is shown with diffused coordinates. Other information about a protected location can also be limited.

recorderCode.description: Name or code for the person conducting the survey. Several names or codes can be given.

recorderOrganisation.description: The organisation that the surveyor represents. Several organisations can be given.

samplingProtocol.description: The survey method used at the specific survey event. The monitoring manual or equivalent methodology is referenced in Dataset C.1.2.

noObservations.description: States whether any of the sought after organisms were observed during the survey event or not. True means that none of the sought after organisms were observed at all.

associatedMedia.description: Attached information about the survey event, e.g. media files like images, sound recordings, maps etc.

occurrenceIds.description: A list of unique identities of the occurances made during an event

Event.description: A specified event when organisms were surveyed according to a specified methodology at a specific place.

skip.description: Ignores the specified number of items and returns a sequence starting at the item after the last skipped item.

totalCount.description: The total number of records matching the query.

maxDistanceFromGeometries.description: The offset in meters from the geometries. This variable is required if geometries type is point

LifeStage.description: Age category or development stage of the observed organism.

locationID.description: A unique id-number for a place, e.g. a survey site or a subsite. Should be the id-number from Stationsregistret where relevant.

locality.description: The name of a survey site or a subsite.

locationRemarks.description: Comment (freetext) from the survey event about the site.

Location.description: Information about a place that has been surveyed.

LocationType.description: "The type of survey site that was surveyed, e.g. square, segment, point site, counting zone, route etc."

methodologyName.description: The title or name of a methodology, e.g. a monitoring manual.

methodologyDescription.description: Short description of a methodology, e.g. a monitoring manual.

methodologyLink.description: Persistent link to description of a methodology, e.g. a monitoring manual.

speciesList.description: Persistent link to published species list for the dataset.

Methodology.description: The methodology that is used for the data collection, e.g. as described by one or more monitoring manuals. Can contain a range of methods for the same and/or different parts of the data collection.

occurrenceID.description: An identifier for the Occurrence (as opposed to a particular digital record of the occurrence). In the absence of a persistent global unique identifier, construct one from a combination of identifiers in the record that will most closely make the occurrenceID globally unique. (Source: Darwin Core quick reference guide)

observationTime.description: The specific time for the specific species observation (local time). (A general time/date for all species observations made during a survey event is given in the object inventeringstillfälle.)

eventEndDate.description: Date and Time for when the survey ended (local time).

quantity.description: Amount of organisms of a certain unit (given in the attribute unit).

observationCertainty.description: States the radius within which the actual observation was made from the most specific coordinates given, i.e. the coordinates for the site, subsite or observation point.

identificationVerificationStatus.description: States the quality of a species observation, i.e. whether its verified by an expert or similar.

associatedMedia.description: Attached information about the species observation, e.g. media files like images, sound recordings etc. Can also be collected physical samples that can be referenced.

eventID.description: A unique identity of the event where the observation were made.

Occurrence.description: A specific observation of an organism or a uniform group of organisms made at an event.

skip.description: Ignores the specified number of items and returns a sequence starting at the item after the last skipped item.

totalCount.description: The total number of records matching the query.

OccurrenceStatus.description: States whether a specific taxon was observed or not. Observations with \"Förekomst\" = \"inte observerad\" are so called zero observations.

OrganismVariable.description: Observed attributes and other variables linked to a certain individual or uniform group of individuals, e.g. sex, age, behavior.

Precipitation.description: States the precipitation conditions during the survey event.

ProgrammeArea.description: The program area within environmental monitoring that the dataset belongs to.

projectID.description: Unique id for the project within which the dataset was collected.

projectCode.description: Name of the project within which the dataset was collected. Can sometimes be the same as the name of the dataset.

ProjectType.description: Type of project that the dataset was collected within, e.g. 'delprogram', 'gemensamt delprogram'.

Purpose.description: The purpose of the data collection (e.g. national or regional environmental monitoring).

QuantityVariable.description: States how the quantity of the observed species (or other taxonomic rank) was counted or measured.

SnowCover.description: States the snow conditions on the ground during the survey event.

taxonID.description: Unique id for species or other given taxon rank according to Dyntaxa.

vernacularName.description: The Swedish name according to Dyntaxa for the observed organism, at the given taxonomic level.

scientificName.description: The scientific name according to Dyntaxa for the observed organism, at the given taxonomic level.

taxonRank.description: The taxonomic level according to Dyntaxa at which the species identification is given.

verbatimName.description: The Swedish name for the observed organism, at the given taxonomic level, as reported by the surveyor. Can be different from now valid taxonomy. (For traceability.)

verbatimTaxonID.description: The id for species or other given level of taxonomy as reported by the surveyor. Can be different from now valid taxonomy. (For traceability.)

Taxon.description: Taxonomic information about the observation. States which species (or subspecies, species aggregation, genus, family etc) was observed and identified.

Unit.description:
Unit for a certain amount of organisms (given in the attribute quantity) or
Unit for a reported measurement (given in the attribute "vädermått")..

Visibility.description: States the visibility conditions during the survey event.

WeatherMeasuring.description: Weather variable reported as a measurement and a unit.

WindDirectionCompass.description: States the wind direction during the survey event as a compass direction.

WindStrength.description: States the strength of the wind during the survey event.
